The Presidential Imbizo is a public-participation platform where communities are able to interact directly with government on challenges in society and where citizens are able to engage on community-generated solutions to such challenges. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa will interact with communities across South Africa through a virtual Presidential Imbizo on coronavirus. The Presidency says due to the COVID-19 pandemic, the Presidential Imbizo will take the form of a virtual engagement in which communities are invited to participate through more than 80 community radio stations, TV channels and social media. "The Presidential Imbizo is a public-participation platform where communities are able to interact directly with government on challenges in society and where citizens are able to engage on community-generated solutions to such challenges," the Presidency said. READ: COVID-19: SANDF medical teams to be deployed to ECape Meanwhile, South Africa's death toll surged by 128 over the past 24-hours. The highest number reported in a single day. The death toll now stands at 2,657. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8 am to 4 pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.